							All Positions in Administration










								There are no open positions in this functional area at this time. 
								Please click on 'Add to cart' above to submit your application for future consideration.
							 






Add to cart							
							All Positions in Design and User Experience









Add to cart							
							Interaction Designer

								
								
									We are seeking an exceptionally able interaction designer for our Hyderabad-based Design and User Experience group to help us design web-based software products that solve users' problems.  This group works closely with development teams, business analysts, and project owners through all the stages of product development. If hired for this position, you would be creating paper prototypes and high-fidelity image mockups for the proposed design concepts, as well as provide HTML, CSS style guides. The candidate will also be responsible for performing heuristics-based UI design reviews and support design choices with reasons and specifics. 

The ideal candidate will have a Bachelor's degree or higher in product design, industrial design or information design from a reputed university.  Minimum 2 years of interface and interaction designing experience is required.  Experience in designing data intensive applications will be a plus.  The candidate must have advanced knowledge of using graphics and prototyping tools, such as Axure, Adobe Photoshop, Illustrator, etc.,. Exposure to HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript frameworks will be preferred.

Additionally, he/she should be flexible to work simultaneously on multiple projects of diverse nature.  Exceptional written and oral communication skills, visual thinking, and ability to effectively communicate design ideas are essentials for this role.
								
							














Add to cart							
							All positions in  Financial Operations









Add to cart							
							Generalist Analyst

								
								
									We are looking for resourceful candidates to join our Financial Operations group based out of the firm's office in Hyderabad, India. The ideal candidate should have a Master's degree in Finance along with up to two years of relevant experience in the financial services industry. The candidate should also have a high level of attention to detail, strong analytical and problem solving skills, and an ability to collaborate well with the other groups. The Financial Operations group is an integral part of our global operations. If hired, you will support one or more of the functions mentioned below: 
- Management Reporting - Team responsibilities include preparing firm-wide P&L reports, handling processes related to expenses and time allocations, and preparing a firm-wide expense budget. The team works closely with senior management including the office of the COO, business unit heads, and portfolio managers to provide key performance metrics for effective decision making. The team analyzes P&L, expenses, capital, returns, fees, taxes, and annual changes in firm-wide and business-unit-level expenses, among others. 
- Pricing - Team responsibilities include understanding the firm's private equity businesses, researching and analyzing a portfolio company's fundamentals, and performing in-depth competitor analysis. The team is responsible for building, updating, and maintaining valuation models that incorporate the terms of the investment and adhere to the accounting/audit guidelines, preparing detailed documentation of valuation methodology, monitoring deal inputs and assumptions for their relevance on a periodic basis, and facilitating deal reviews by third parties. 
- Investor Relations - Team responsibilities include maintaining and processing various transactions (withdrawals, subscriptions, etc.) at an investor level and drafting customized documents for a variety of transactions. This team interacts extensively with our investors and their respective administrators/custodians. The team is responsible for preparing several reports that are eventually used by senior management. The team also works closely with consultants/relationship mangers to market our Institutional Asset Management side of the business. 
- Compliance - This team works closely with the global Compliance team to support day-to-day management of the firm's compliance program, including implementing and enforcing policies and procedures that align both with the internal Code of Ethics as well as any external rules and regulations. The team is also involved in various regulatory filing obligations and in monitoring and implementing controls designed to ensure compliance with global rules and regulations (such as those concerning insider trading prevention, anti-money laundering ("AML"), and global trading restrictions).
								
							









Add to cart							
							Industrial Trainees - ICAI

								
								
