Primary responsibilities will include:

-Supporting front-office traders/analysts on critical and time-sensitive recurring tasks that are data intensive in nature.
-Build and manage large financial data sets; perform exception analysis.
-Collaborating with the in-house technology team to automate processes to achieve optimal efficiency. 
-Support the Fundamental Research team in Hyderabad by conducting data research, summarizing industry/company conference calls, and preparing quarterly earnings reports.  

The ideal candidate should have a Master's degree in Business or Finance along with 3-6 years of experience in financial operations. Additionally, he/she should be self-motivated, possess strong analytical and leadership qualities as well as be able to work independently with limited direction and guidance.  Good verbal and written communication skills are required.
E-mail this position























Management Company Accounting







































There are no open positions in this functional area at this time.













 


